<node id="Spect">
  <data key="d0">Spect</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">SPECT (Single Photon Emission Computed Tomography) is a nuclear medicine imaging technique used to overcome the low resolution of conventional nuclear medicine imaging.&lt;SEP&gt;Spect is a medical imaging technique used to examine the function of organs inside the human body, involving radiopharmaceuticals labeled with radioisotopes.&lt;SEP&gt;A tomographic imaging technique that includes all diagnostic information of Planar image.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1f7b7855d5cca22ae703580be0fcfc7f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5c780a124da5a0a162247f1f1afa55b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a8d83cceadb557de5590c9a00dcc986e</data>
