<node id="핵의학">
  <data key="d0">핵의학</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">핵의학 (nuclear medicine) is a discipline that diagnoses the physiological and pathological state of the body using γ-rays or β-rays and treats with unsealed radioactive sources.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b06ed9f5e0dd9cd85ffaf0fc38757627</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775522907</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="핵의학진단법">
  <data key="d0">핵의학진단법</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">핵의학진단법 (nuclear medicine diagnostic method) measures functional changes rather than anatomical changes and observes biochemical changes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b06ed9f5e0dd9cd85ffaf0fc38757627</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775522907</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="체내검사">
  <data key="d0">체내검사</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">체내검사 (In vivo study) involves directly injecting radiopharmaceuticals into the human body to analyze the accumulation and excretion of radioactive material in organs, both statically and dynamically.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b06ed9f5e0dd9cd85ffaf0fc38757627</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775522907</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="핵의학영상분야">
  <data key="d0">핵의학영상분야</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">핵의학영상분야 (nuclear medicine imaging field) measures the pathological and physiological changes of the human body.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b06ed9f5e0dd9cd85ffaf0fc38757627</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775522907</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="체외검사">
  <data key="d0">체외검사</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">체외검사 (In vitro study) involves collecting samples (blood, urine, etc.) from a patient, diluting them with radioactive material, and then performing quantitative analysis.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b06ed9f5e0dd9cd85ffaf0fc38757627</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775522907</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="방사면역측정법">
  <data key="d0">방사면역측정법</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">방사면역측정법 (Radioimmuno Assay; RIA) measures the concentration of antigens using reactions in test tubes and radioactive tracers.&lt;SEP&gt;Radioimmunoassay (RIA) was developed by Berson and Yalow in 1959.&lt;SEP&gt;방사면역측정법 is used for quantitative analysis of trace amounts of substances (e.g., hormones) in blood.&lt;SEP&gt;방사면역측정법 is a radioimmunoassay technique.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b06ed9f5e0dd9cd85ffaf0fc38757627&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-72590c67e60a69d417d259ef71baaf90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-924d4e084e2a6643308b6bc76af06895&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-01aeb670194fbaa7323582a61264ce3a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523009</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="방사성동위원소치료">
  <data key="d0">방사성동위원소치료</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">방사성동위원소치료 (Radioisotope Therapy) involves administering radiopharmaceuticals into the body to accumulate in lesions and treating them with selective radiation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b06ed9f5e0dd9cd85ffaf0fc38757627</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775522907</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="핵종">
  <data key="d0">핵종</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">핵종 (nuclide) refers to a specific atomic nucleus characterized by its atomic number and mass number.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b06ed9f5e0dd9cd85ffaf0fc38757627</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775522907</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="동위원소">
  <data key="d0">동위원소</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">동위원소 (Isotope) refers to elements with the same atomic number but different mass numbers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b06ed9f5e0dd9cd85ffaf0fc38757627</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775522907</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="정적영상">
  <data key="d0">정적영상</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">정적영상 (static image) is acquired at a specific time after injection into the human body.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b06ed9f5e0dd9cd85ffaf0fc38757627</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775522907</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="동적영상">
  <data key="d0">동적영상</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">동적영상 (dynamic image) tracks the movement or metabolic processes within the body according to changes in time.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b06ed9f5e0dd9cd85ffaf0fc38757627</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775522907</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Biochemical Changes">
  <data key="d0">Biochemical Changes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Biochemical Changes refers to alterations at the molecular level within the body that can be observed using nuclear medicine diagnostic methods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b06ed9f5e0dd9cd85ffaf0fc38757627</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775522907</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
