<node id="감마카메라">
  <data key="d0">감마카메라</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">감마카메라, also known as a gamma camera or scintillation camera, is a type of imaging device used for capturing gamma ray images. The gamma camera is a type of image recording device. In procedures using a gamma camera, radionuclides that emit γ-ray energy of 80-200 keV are used. It was developed by Anger in 1958 and became commercially available in 1964. The gamma camera's intrinsic efficiency is a primary factor that affects it.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-72590c67e60a69d417d259ef71baaf90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07321f301db639ed7357619e9557e638&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fda9da9d7fcaa192c940b687cf738dd0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e10d247e7c97528d1ea50ec0eb927f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78dbaba6777799b28327851a2d931cc2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-08708d5929cf7059523d87243b280f2c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73fd9633bf193d21c88e0cf35c08d9fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-475783fc231bbcff930d8d8bc16de315</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
