<node id="Radioimmuno Therapy">
  <data key="d0">Radioimmuno Therapy</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Radioimmuno therapy is a treatment method using radiolabeled monoclonal antibodies against tumor-specific antigens.&lt;SEP&gt;Radioimmuno Therapy involves labeling monoclonal antibodies with beta emitters such as 90Y, 91Y, and 186Re for treating malignant tumors.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-72590c67e60a69d417d259ef71baaf90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a8d3df39b55d27db11892fbbfe761c8</data>
