<node id="Pet Scanner">
  <data key="d0">Pet Scanner</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The Pet Scanner makes images by converting gamma rays emitted from radioactive drugs into light, consists of detectors, signal processing systems, and a simultaneous counting circuit that detects gamma rays emitted when positrons are annihilated, and uses a high-performance computer that can control the scanner, reconstruct images, and analyze and express images.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-428583e70d87d887ad563511e218180d</data>
