<node id="99Mo">
  <data key="d0">99Mo</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
  <data key="d2">99Mo is a radioactive isotope of molybdenum (몰리브덴의 방사성 동위원소) produced in a nuclear reactor. It is notably produced by the Hanaro reactor for use in nuclear medicine testing. 99Mo serves as the parent radionuclide in a generator, where it is adsorbed onto an alumina column in the 99Mo–99mTc Generator. From this, the 99mTcO4- solution is eluted. 99Mo has a half-life of approximately 66 hours (specifically, 66.7 hours). It emits gamma rays with energies of 41 keV (1.3%), 141 keV (5.6%), 181 keV (1.5%), and 366 keV (1.5%), and its Rhm value is 0.092.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-428583e70d87d887ad563511e218180d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-924d4e084e2a6643308b6bc76af06895&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fda9da9d7fcaa192c940b687cf738dd0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fd28894fc7b2a8aeb26f735075d67fb8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-35a6e76b25728f999d21671d0895170a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dfe1a1928a0c8fd37b6094e61031eb3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ae44ccfebfa3151a87d3796eb87d286e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dadb2dd7986d02d7bbf1f38dea49af99</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523125</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cyclotron">
  <data key="d0">Cyclotron</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Cyclotron is a device used for producing radioisotopes for PET/CT.&lt;SEP&gt;A cyclotron is used to produce short-lived radioactive isotopes such as 11C, 13N, and 15O.&lt;SEP&gt;Cyclotron used for radiopharmaceutical production.&lt;SEP&gt;Cyclotron is a particle accelerator needed to produce radioisotopes for PET.&lt;SEP&gt;Cyclotron is a device that artificially creates radioactive nuclides by colliding high-energy charged particles with a target material.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-428583e70d87d887ad563511e218180d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d83407b553bdad56b98cf8fd5be64bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fda9da9d7fcaa192c940b687cf738dd0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83b2ddf22a61c92feb5b93c9cf9b98eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0782c64fcf3afb545cd9c3f803922e58</data>
