<node id="NaI(Tl)">
  <data key="d0">NaI(Tl)</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
  <data key="d2">NaI(Tl) is a type of inorganic scintillator that has good fluorescence efficiency and low self-absorption of scintillation within the scintillator. Its output pulse varies in proportion to the radiation energy absorbed in the scintillator.&lt;SEP&gt;NaI(Tl) is a type of inorganic scintillator.&lt;SEP&gt;NaI(Tl)은 감마를 측정한다.&lt;SEP&gt;NaI(Tl) is a scintillator widely used in SPECT, which emits visible light when interacting with gamma rays.&lt;SEP&gt;NaI(Tl) is a thallium-doped sodium iodide scintillator used in SPECT.&lt;SEP&gt;NaI(Tl)는 BGO, LSO, YSO와 비교되는 섬광검출기 재료임.&lt;SEP&gt;Sodium iodide doped with thallium, a scintillation material.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6259ff245a0935f93363f0b914c89df9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6950680210b027776828c422863fe88&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78dbaba6777799b28327851a2d931cc2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a1e99e5d45d87bc110fb72539f81b91d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83b2ddf22a61c92feb5b93c9cf9b98eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50349fd89c39a44e7081da426038f848&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04bcfb8da445fd49f5c837b6179c61bb</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523306</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="CsI(Tl)">
  <data key="d0">CsI(Tl)</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">CsI(Tl) is an inorganic scintillator with higher density and effective atomic number than NaI(Tl), resulting in higher gamma-ray detection efficiency, but lower energy resolution.&lt;SEP&gt;CsI(Tl) is a type of inorganic scintillator.&lt;SEP&gt;CsI(Tl)은 감마를 측정한다.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6259ff245a0935f93363f0b914c89df9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6950680210b027776828c422863fe88&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78dbaba6777799b28327851a2d931cc2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523166</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="LiI(Eu)">
  <data key="d0">LiI(Eu)</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">LiI(Eu) is an inorganic scintillator used for thermal neutron detection through the thermal neutron-induced nuclear reaction 6Li(n,α)3H.&lt;SEP&gt;LiI(Eu) is a type of inorganic scintillator.&lt;SEP&gt;LiI(Eu)는 열중성자를 측정한다.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6259ff245a0935f93363f0b914c89df9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6950680210b027776828c422863fe88&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78dbaba6777799b28327851a2d931cc2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523166</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ZnS(Ag)">
  <data key="d0">ZnS(Ag)</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">ZnS(Ag) is an inorganic scintillator with very high scintillation efficiency, used in polycrystalline powder form for alpha-ray counting. It is also used for fast neutron measurement by mixing ZnS with acrylic resin.&lt;SEP&gt;ZnS(Ag) is a type of inorganic scintillator.&lt;SEP&gt;ZnS(Ag)는 알파를 측정한다.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6259ff245a0935f93363f0b914c89df9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e6950680210b027776828c422863fe88&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78dbaba6777799b28327851a2d931cc2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523166</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="KI(Tl)">
  <data key="d0">KI(Tl)</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">KI(Tl) is a type of inorganic scintillator.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6259ff245a0935f93363f0b914c89df9</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523166</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="BGO">
  <data key="d0">BGO</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">BGO is a type of inorganic scintillator.&lt;SEP&gt;BGO는 NaI(Tl)보다 밀도와 실효원자번호가 높아 우수한 감마선 저지능을 가지고 있어 소멸방사선의 감약률이 크고 검출효율이 높지만, 발광효율이 NaI(Tl)의 약 20%로 낮으며 섬광감쇠시간이 300 ns로 길다.&lt;SEP&gt;Bismuth germanate oxide, a scintillation material.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6259ff245a0935f93363f0b914c89df9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50349fd89c39a44e7081da426038f848&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04bcfb8da445fd49f5c837b6179c61bb</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523306</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="GSO">
  <data key="d0">GSO</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">GSO is a type of inorganic scintillator.&lt;SEP&gt;GSO는 GEMINI TF (PHILIPS)에 사용되는 물질이다.&lt;SEP&gt;Gadolinium silicate oxide, a scintillation material.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6259ff245a0935f93363f0b914c89df9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50349fd89c39a44e7081da426038f848&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04bcfb8da445fd49f5c837b6179c61bb</data>
