</node>
<node id="Pb">
  <data key="d0">Pb</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
  <data key="d2">Pb (lead), alloyed with antimony and bismuth, is used as a shielding material in collimators due to its high radiation absorption.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-08708d5929cf7059523d87243b280f2c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523200</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Collimator">
  <data key="d0">Collimator</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A collimator is a device used to filter, focus, or direct a beam of radiation or particles. Specifically in the context of gamma ray detection, it is designed to direct radiation from a target organ and detect only gamma rays from a specific direction. It geometrically limits gamma rays emitted from the scan area, allowing only those from the necessary area to interact with the NaI(Tl) crystal. Also referred to as 조준기(jo-jun-gi), the collimator is a device used to collimate radiation. The choice of collimator impacts 감도 (sensitivity) and 해상력 (resolution), and the appropriate collimator must be selected for each energy level. Notably, a collimator is not used in Positron Emission Tomography (PET) scans in order to enhance detection efficiency, and it may be either attached or removed during uniformity measurements.&lt;SEP&gt;Collimator는 간격 3cm, 내경 약 2mm 이하의 납격자상 phantom을 평행으로 놓고 그 상을 영상화하는 장치이다.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-08708d5929cf7059523d87243b280f2c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-73fd9633bf193d21c88e0cf35c08d9fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-97bd5e81d74ceb332b6540d68a9844dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-abfdeda3e4621d85e0f953a3a7cee2a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a1e99e5d45d87bc110fb72539f81b91d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5c780a124da5a0a162247f1f1afa55b8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b90292f9431fa43f118e063f626e7413&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-34f62ef495ef155167a515f56fca8173&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-475783fc231bbcff930d8d8bc16de315</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523378</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Multihole Focusing Collimator">
  <data key="d0">Multihole Focusing Collimator</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Multihole focusing collimators are commonly used collimators.&lt;SEP&gt;Multihole focusing collimators are a type of collimator.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-08708d5929cf7059523d87243b280f2c</data>
