<node id="Parallel Multihole Collimator">
  <data key="d0">Parallel Multihole Collimator</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A collimator made of lead with many parallel holes, commonly used in imaging. It maintains a constant image size regardless of the source distance but needs to be close to the source for high sensitivity and resolution. It is classified into high and low energy types for Brain, Liver, and Kidney imaging.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6275b489d31d3ddb70252ffd8be243b7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523224</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="High Energy Collimator">
  <data key="d0">High Energy Collimator</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A collimator with few holes, thick septa, and long holes, used for high-energy isotopes (e.g., 131I).</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6275b489d31d3ddb70252ffd8be243b7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523224</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Medium Energy Collimator">
  <data key="d0">Medium Energy Collimator</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A collimator with characteristics between high and low energy collimators, used for medium-energy isotopes (e.g., 67Ga, 111In, 123I).</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6275b489d31d3ddb70252ffd8be243b7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523224</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Low Energy Collimator">
  <data key="d0">Low Energy Collimator</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A collimator with many holes and thin septa, used for low-energy isotopes. Hole diameters are typically 1.5-3mm (e.g., 99mTc, 201Tl, 133Xe, 125I).</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6275b489d31d3ddb70252ffd8be243b7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523225</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Diverging Collimator">
  <data key="d0">Diverging Collimator</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A collimator that expands the field of view while reducing the image size, but has poor resolution in the periphery.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6275b489d31d3ddb70252ffd8be243b7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523225</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Converging Collimator">
  <data key="d0">Converging Collimator</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A collimator that narrows the field of view while enlarging the image size. It has high resolution but resolution varies with organ depth.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6275b489d31d3ddb70252ffd8be243b7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523225</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Slant Hole Collimator">
  <data key="d0">Slant Hole Collimator</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A collimator with image size and resolution similar to a parallel collimator. It is useful for positioning in cardiac examinations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6275b489d31d3ddb70252ffd8be243b7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523225</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pinhole Collimator">
  <data key="d0">Pinhole Collimator</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A collimator that generally magnifies the image size and has high resolution. It is used for imaging small organs such as the thyroid gland but has poor sensitivity.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6275b489d31d3ddb70252ffd8be243b7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523225</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Scintillator">
  <data key="d0">Scintillator</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A material that converts photon energy into scintillation.&lt;SEP&gt;A scintillator is a material that emits light when exposed to ionizing radiation.&lt;SEP&gt;Scintillator is a material that emits light when it interacts with ionizing radiation, used with γ선.&lt;SEP&gt;Scintillation material.&lt;SEP&gt;Scintillator는 계수 효율에 영향을 미치는 요소이다.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6275b489d31d3ddb70252ffd8be243b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-03574e2708590c1fbd812aab77b1c581&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83b2ddf22a61c92feb5b93c9cf9b98eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04bcfb8da445fd49f5c837b6179c61bb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-475783fc231bbcff930d8d8bc16de315</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523379</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Nal(Tl) Crystal">
