  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">FWHM (Full Width at Half Maximum) is used to represent resolution.&lt;SEP&gt;FWHM (full width at half maximum) is a common method for expressing spatial resolution.&lt;SEP&gt;FWHM (반치폭) is a method to represent spatial resolution.&lt;SEP&gt;FWHM (반치폭) is used to measure LSF (line spread function).</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a1e99e5d45d87bc110fb72539f81b91d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7388f7ee8e7e66b19833edd200caba00&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-34f62ef495ef155167a515f56fca8173&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-435f46f7df27683a6f082e9ae451704b</data>
