<node id="Spatial Resolution">
  <data key="d0">Spatial Resolution</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Spatial Resolution is the maximum ability of the Scinti-Camera to distinguish between objects.&lt;SEP&gt;Spatial Resolution is the ability of a scinti-camera to distinguish two point or line sources as separate entities.&lt;SEP&gt;Spatial Resolution is an important parameter in SPECT quality control.&lt;SEP&gt;Spatial Resolution refers to 해상력, which is assessed in scinticameras and is evaluated using various methods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7388f7ee8e7e66b19833edd200caba00&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-34f62ef495ef155167a515f56fca8173&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-435f46f7df27683a6f082e9ae451704b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-833544a0af4106771fa805c95df67753</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523380</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Bar Phantom">
  <data key="d0">Bar Phantom</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The Bar Phantom is used to visually assess the minimum distinguishable unit.&lt;SEP&gt;Bar phantom is a tool used to assess spatial resolution.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7388f7ee8e7e66b19833edd200caba00&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-34f62ef495ef155167a515f56fca8173</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
