  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The Hole Phantom is used to visually assess the minimum distinguishable unit.&lt;SEP&gt;Hole phantom is a tool used to assess spatial resolution.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7388f7ee8e7e66b19833edd200caba00&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-34f62ef495ef155167a515f56fca8173</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523343</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="System Spatial Resolution (Rs)">
  <data key="d0">System Spatial Resolution (Rs)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">System Spatial Resolution (Rs) is the resolution of the system, which is related to the resolution of the device (Ri) and the resolution of the collimator (Rc).</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7388f7ee8e7e66b19833edd200caba00</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523343</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Device Resolution (Ri)">
  <data key="d0">Device Resolution (Ri)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Device Resolution (Ri) is the resolution of the device.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7388f7ee8e7e66b19833edd200caba00</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775523343</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
